    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Fire's Deadly Sin</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img style="width: 200px; height: 200px;" title="fire's_deadly_sin_incantation_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/fires_ deadly_sin_incantation_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="fires deadly sin incantation elden ring wiki guide 200px" width="200" height="200"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Spell Type</td> 
     <td><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Fire Monk Incantations" href="/Fire+Monk+Incantations" target="">Fire Monk Incantation</a></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>FP Cost 26</td> 
     <td>Slots Used 1</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td colspan="2"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft">
        Sets area and self ablaze with raging flames 
      </div> <br><img style="float: left;" title="Attributes Requirement" src="/file/Elden-Ring/attributes-required-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="attributes required elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">Requires 
      <div class="lineleft"> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence" target="">Intelligence</a> 0 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a> 19 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Arcane" href="/Arcane" target="">Arcane</a> 0 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Fire's Deadly Sin</strong> is an <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Incantations" href="/Incantations" target="">Incantation</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. <strong>Fire's Deadly Sin spell</strong> covers both the player and the area with flames</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Incantation originating from a deeply ominous prophecy.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Sets both the caster and the surrounding area ablaze with raging flames. The caster's body will remain engulfed in flame for a while, burning them and any who draw near. Charging enhances potency.</em></p> 
 <p><em>The prophet despaired, looking up at the Erdtree, for soon the kindling would burst into flame, bringing ruin.</em></p> 
 <p><em>"The burning of the Erdtree is the first cardinal sin. That is not the domain of mere men."</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Fire's Deadly Sin</h3> 
<p>Where to find <strong>Fire's Deadly Sin</strong>:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Acquire the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Flightless Bird Painting" href="/Flightless+Bird+Painting">Flightless Bird Painting</a>&nbsp;from Fortified Manor, Leyndell, Royal Capital.</li> 
 <li>Then go&nbsp;southeast of&nbsp;Windmill Heights, directly East of where is says Dominula,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Windmill Village" href="/Windmill+Village" target="">Windmill Village</a>&nbsp;on the map. You'll see a ghost in a chair who will drop it after disappearing.&nbsp; [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=6365&amp;lat=-80.41406&amp;lng=101.20763&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=6365&amp;lat=-80.41406&amp;lng=101.20763&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Interactive Map link</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Fire's Deadly Sin Guide</h3> 
<p>&nbsp;Reward from completing the "Flightless Bird" painting puzzle.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Stamina Cost: 28</li> 
 <li>Deals fire damage</li> 
 <li>Duration: 40 Seconds</li> 
 <li>Continually deals fire damage to both&nbsp;the caster and enemies that are at least within dagger range of the player.</li> 
 <li>As a continuous source of fire damage it can reliably reset the Frostbite status effect on enemies for build that inflict frost bite rapidly.</li> 
 <li>Wearing the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Royal Remains Set" href="/Royal+Remains+Set">Royal Remains Set</a> ensures the caster will never be killed by the DoT this incantation inflicts. The <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Blessed Dew Talisman" href="/Blessed+Dew+Talisman">Blessed Dew Talisman</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Blessing's Boon" href="/Blessing's+Boon">Blessing's Boon</a>/<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Blessing of the Erdtree" href="/Blessing+of+the+Erdtree">Blessing of the Erdtree</a>&nbsp;incantation, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Icon Shield" href="/Icon+Shield">Icon Shield</a> or <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Crimsonburst Crystal Tear" href="/Crimsonburst+Crystal+Tear">Crimsonburst Crystal Tear</a> can also mitigate it.</li> 
 <li>This is a&nbsp;<strong>Body&nbsp;</strong><strong>Buff</strong>&nbsp;and will not&nbsp;stack with other buffs of the same type. 
  <ul> 
   <li>See&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Buffs and Debuffs" href="/Buffs+and+Debuffs" target="">Buffs and Debuffs</a>&nbsp;for more information on stacking buffs.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
