				<li id="16728615" class="cmnt-root" data="37" data-d="1656897903000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579641/Fire's-Deadly-Sin" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">03 Jul 2022 21:25</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16728615" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">As of 1.05, some of what works on this has changed. Here&apos;s a list based on my testing:<br/>Thing&apos;s I&apos;ve tested that *do* apply:<br/>- Talismans that boost damage: fire scorpion charm, godfrey icon (only if charged), red-feathered branchsword, lord of blood&apos;s exultation, kindred of rot&apos;s exultation<br/>- Incantation buffs that apply a special status: bloodflame blade, black flame blade (only applies status, doesn&apos;t increase damage)<br/>- Status-inflicting buffs from SOME NON-UNIQUE weapon skills: poisonous mist, chilling mist (repeatedly procs frostbite!), but NOT seppuku<br/>- The fire-shrouding cracked tear<br/>- Aura buffs, such as golden vow or rallying standard<br/>- The jellyfish shield&apos;s contagious fury skill<br/>- Other equipment buffs, such as the twinbird kite shield, white mask, and mushroom crown<br/><br/>Things that *do not* apply:<br/>- Great stars/butchering knife heals on hit (removed in this patch, if earlier comments are correct)<br/>- Straightforward damaging buffs from spells, consumables, or ashes of war, such as lightning weapon, fire grease, or sacred blade<br/>- Status-inflicting buffs from spells or consumables, such as poison weapon or rot grease<br/>- Status-inflicting buffs from *unique* weapon skills (as best I can tell), such as the eclipse shotel&apos;s death flare or the dragonscale blade&apos;s ice lightning sword.<br/>- Seppuku&apos;s weapon buff.<br/><br/>Base damage is 5 per tick uncharged, 9 per tick charged on the celebrants in windmill village who have 0 fire absorption according to datamined stat sheets.<br/>With the jellyfish shield, golden vow, fire scorpion charm, godfrey&apos;s icon, red branchsword, blood exultation and white mask triggered with seppuku, the fire cracked tear, and the twinbird kite shield, I got 33 damage per tick, which is almost *four times* the base and only slightly less than the max as far as I know (would require using rot exultation instead of fire scorpion charm). <br/>I made a contact damage only build with the briar set and some of the above. The weapon buffs make the build WAY more effective, but are likely exploits, so only use them in PvE if you choose to. Hope this helped some of you who also want to minmax this janky spell!</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16728615" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16728615" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>38</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16728615"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16728615" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"