				<li id="16720607" class="cmnt-root" data="69" data-d="1655806252000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579641/Fire's-Deadly-Sin" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">21 Jun 2022 06:10</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16720607" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Did some testing on the buff (As a response to a previous comment, but replies on this site have non-existent formatting):<br/><br/>The buff ticks every 0.5 seconds.<br/><br/>Self damage is 3 per tick uncharged and 4 per tick charged. This self damage is not actually damage, but rather, negative regen so it is unaffected by damage negations.<br/><br/>Buff is unaffected by incant scaling. Testing with 99 Fth Erdtree Seal +10 (367 Inc Scal) and Finger Seal +0 (183 Inc Scal) it did the same damage.<br/><br/>Damage of the buff is 6 damage per tick uncharged and 10 per tick charged.<br/><br/>The damage is affected by Golden Vow, Fire Scorpion Charm and Flame-Shrouding Cracked Tear.<br/><br/>It is NOT affected by Canvas Talismans (I checked with Golden Vow too to see if it was perhaps just not showing the damage increase because 8% of 10 damage would be 0.8 which would likely get rounded down. With Golden Vow&apos;s 15% damage increase, that 8% would stack to push it over 20% which would provide a full interger increase. But alas it did nothing)<br/><br/>Each source of damage increase (The talisman, the physick and the buff) increases the damage by 1 point uncharged and 2 points charged:<br/><br/>Uncharged: 6 damage<br/>With Flame Scorpion: 7 damage<br/>With Flame Scorpion and Physick: 8 damage<br/>With Flame Scorpion, Physick and Golden Vow: 9 damage<br/><br/>Charged: 10 damage<br/>With Flame Scorpion: 12 damage<br/>With Flame Scorpion and Physick: 14 damage<br/>With Flame Scorpion, Physick and Golden Vow: 16 damage<br/><br/>The maximum damage I was able to achieve was 19 damage per tick using Flame Scorpion Talisman, Flame-Shrouded Cracked Tear, Rallying Standard and Shriek of Milos.<br/><br/>Before you ask, no, it is not affected by Flame, Grant Me Strength, as both are body buffs and so they remove each other when cast.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16720607" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16720607" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>69</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16720607"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16720607" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16720607"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
