				<li id="16663527" class="cmnt-root" data="6" data-d="1651470509000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579641/Fire's-Deadly-Sin" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">02 May 2022 01:48</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16663527" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This spell has its niche uses. By itself it&apos;s lackluster. Tiny damage while hurting yourself? Pass. But when used with a frostbite weapon, it allows frostbite to work like bleed. The AoE fire effect will dispel frostbite on your target and allow you to reapply it, dealing the burst damage over again. I found it particularly useful by pairing an inherit frostbite weapon like Dragonscale Katana with a blood infused Uchigatana. Apply both their statuses consistently and since they&apos;re different status ailments, bosses don&apos;t build up a high tolerance fast like how bleed does with more and more bleed bar required every time it procs. Also removes frostbite on yourself, which is nice.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16663527" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16663527" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>7</p